1) Download the desired UF tgz package to the static/ folder.  Example:

wget -O splunkforwarder-8.0.4-767223ac207f-Linux-x86_64.tgz 'https://www.splunk.com/bin/splunk/DownloadActivityServlet?architecture=x86_64&platform=linux&version=8.0.4&product=universalforwarder&filename=splunkforwarder-8.0.4-767223ac207f-Linux-x86_64.tgz&wget=true'

2) Edit	bin/upgrade-wrapper.sh, set filename of tgz file

3) Edit	bin/upgrade-wrapper.sh, set version of tgz file

4) Edit bin/upgrade.sh, set BACKUP_LOC & LOG_FILE with respective file location

5) Edit local/inputs.conf, set appropriate index, source & sourcetype for the inputs

Note:

This app can also be pushed from Deployment Server to Linux Universal forwarders to upgrade Splunk version in an automated way.

Automation upgrade sample steps:

Steps to Upgrade UF for Linux:

1)      On DS: Place the above app under $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/deployment-apps/ & configure serverclass.conf as below

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Serverclass.conf on DS:

#Linux On-prem UF Upgrade
[serverClass:upgrade_uf_nix]
whitelist.0=<UFHOST1|UFHOST2>

[serverClass:upgrade_uf_nix:app:upgrade_uf_nix]
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

2)      Reload serverclass by running the following command on DS

$SPLUNK_HOME/splunk reload deploy-server -class upgrade_uf_nix

3)      Verify the script execution by running the following search on SH:

SPL: index=_internal host=<UFHOST> source=*splunkd.log component=ExecProcessor “*upgrade-wrapper.sh*"

4)      Verify the version of Splunk UF by running $SPLUNK_HOME/splunk version

5)      Confirm the upgrade is successful by running the following search

SPL: index=main host=<UFHOST> sourcetype=upgrade.log

6)      Verify the backup file is created under the following location

                On UF: /$SPLUNK_HOME/<UFHOST>.tar.gz
